feat(git): Add auto-generated commit message based on Conventional Commits specification.

 
The auto-generated commit message will be based on the configuration in the autodocs.yaml file. This commit introduces the following changes:

* Added a new GitCommit model to the config_model.py file to store configuration for auto-generated commit messages.
* Added a new GitMaster class in the git_master.py file to handle git operations, including generating commit messages.
* Updated the config_parser.py file to parse the GitCommit model from the autodocs.yaml file.
* Updated the YAMLConfig class in the config_parser.py file to include the sysprompt file path for the commit message.
* Updated the autodocs.yaml file to include the configuration for auto-generated commit messages.

BREAKING CHANGE: The auto-generated commit message will now be based on the Conventional Commits specification. This may change the format of commit messages generated by the tool.